description:
Food: tasty;
Ambience: noisy, VERY NOISY;
Decor/design: trendy;
Major negative: Extremely uncomfortable seating;

We enjoyed the food. However  having no choice but to sit on backless wooden pickle barrels the height of kindergarten chairs, my partner and myself found our knees and backs quite twisted after dinner.

My advice is: if you have any knee, back or other joint problems, DON'T go to this place. 
Also if you want to have any sort of dinner conversation, you probably shouldn't go to this place.
